{"TopicId":146533,"ForumId":66,"TopicTitle":"Devnote Thursday: Tweaking and Turning Gears","CreatedByName":"SQUAD","CreatedById":66485,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T18:43:25Z","PageNum":3,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jarin","CreatedById":71395,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:15:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729640\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472153798\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere it is. Who had \u0022Reply #6\u0022 in the betting pool?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes it count as fudging the betting pool if I had reply #4 too, but waited to mention it? \u0026lt;.\u0026lt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KSK","CreatedById":61025,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:17:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat news all round! It\u0027s one of the smaller points but the EVA camera reorientation toggle will be a much appreciated quality of life improvement for me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OrbitalBuzzsaw","CreatedById":158329,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:22:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729761\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472158170\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022eddiew\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n33 minutes ago, eddiew said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...not so sure about reduced probe control. I feel like the top tier cores should be considered bleeding-edge autonomous and have no problems with touching down on vacuum bodies without a connection to home. Heck, NASA got Viking down on Mars with 0.1% atmospheric density, it can\u0027t be\u00A0impossible for kerbals... Do what you want with the Stayputnik, it\u0027s dead to me already \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith you on that one! Although personally I think that we shouldn\u0027t have this whole stock RemoteTech thing at all, it\u0027s a bad precedent.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-25T21:23:34Z\u0022 title=\u002208/25/2016 09:23  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by OrbitalBuzzsaw\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:25:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729561\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472150605\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266485\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SQUAD\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, SQUAD said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfixed a long-standing issue with Kerbals sliding on ladders.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHallelujah!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbuvim","CreatedById":160177,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:25:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729679\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472154729\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022adsii1970\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, adsii1970 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSquad is aware of the numerous issues and to simply say they do not care about PS4 players is not only unfair, it is dishonest. This company has always supported those within the KSP community better than any other I\u0027ve seen.\u00A0 Just give them time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you want to know what it means \u0022user support\u0022? Here is an example from the developers of \u003Cu\u003Efree(!) \u00A0PS4 (with platfomholder certification!)\u003C/u\u003E \u00A0Warframe, after another huge (4 GB) \u00A0free add-on,\u00A0released in August 16th (sic!)\u00A0:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong style=\u0022font-weight:bold;\u0022\u003EHotfix August 16th\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n- Fixed flipped emblem while using Obsidian Dendra armor\u003Cbr\u003E\n-\u00A0Changed Nekros\u2019 Despoil Augment to reflect his Desecrate changes.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Removed unnecessary Anti-aliasing\u00A0option.\u003Cbr\u003E\n-\u00A0Fixed Nekros\u0027\u00A0Desecrate sound not playing and the FX showing when not needed.\u003Cbr\u003E\n-\u00A0Fixed Sortie missions switching to incorrect Factions.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Fixed seeing \u0027Daily Mission Bonus\u0027 on the End of Mission screen upon failing the mission.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong style=\u0022font-weight:bold;\u0022\u003EHotfix August 17th:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Backend stuff\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong style=\u0022font-weight:bold;\u0022\u003EHotfix August 18th:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Fixed a script error when viewing some blueprints in the arsenal\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Fixed some accounts that were soft banned because of an issues caused by a previous hotfix\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong style=\u0022font-weight:bold;\u0022\u003EHotfix 2 August 18th:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Removed \u0022attachment\u0022 option in the appearance menu for Arcata\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong style=\u0022font-weight:bold;\u0022\u003EHotfix August 19th:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Fixed data mass in Mobile D missions spawning inside the ground.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Fixed corpus turrets not being destroyed properly\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong style=\u0022font-weight:bold;\u0022\u003EHotfix 2 August 19th:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Fixed freeze that would occur after completing a junction\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong style=\u0022font-weight:bold;\u0022\u003EHotfix August 23rd:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Added new Prime Access items!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-bottom:0px;color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong style=\u0022font-weight:bold;\u0022\u003EHotfix August 24th:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Fixed Vaulted relics still dropping\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Fixed Nekros Prime diorama\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-25T21:37:02Z\u0022 title=\u002208/25/2016 09:37  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Kerbuvim\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jarin","CreatedById":71395,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:25:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729761\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472158170\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022eddiew\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, eddiew said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...not so sure about reduced probe control. I feel like the top tier cores should be considered bleeding-edge autonomous and have no problems with touching down on vacuum bodies without a connection to home. Heck, NASA got Viking down on Mars with 0.1% atmospheric density, it can\u0027t be\u00A0impossible for kerbals... Do what you want with the Stayputnik, it\u0027s dead to me already \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTop tier cores have \u0022target\u0022 and \u0022maneuver\u0022 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E options, in addition to all the others, which makes them very easy to pilot with only local\u00A0control. If you need less thrust, you can modify the engine\u0027s max thrust directly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-25T21:26:43Z\u0022 title=\u002208/25/2016 09:26  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Jarin\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dunbaratu","CreatedById":63481,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:26:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729643\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472153905\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002275006\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NathanKell\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, NathanKell said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, just to reinforce \u003Cstrong\u003Eagain\u003C/strong\u003E and be perfectly clear: \u003Cstrong\u003Ethese locks will not interfere with mods\u003C/strong\u003E. Period. We are not setting a flybywire controller, we are not locking actual actions (just GUI actions and keypresses).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about the lock on creating maneuver nodes when out of contact?\u00A0 As far as I remember there were no values in the ControlLocks enum for whether you\u0027re allowed to set a maneuver node (have they been added for 1.2?), and it feels a bit different than the other things covered by the inputlocks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill kOS still be able to do this and have it work if the vessel is out of contact at the time?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E// (v is of type Vessel)\nv.patchedConicSolver.AddManeuverNode(time);\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Angelo Kerman","CreatedById":106975,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:26:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/105198-roverdude/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022105198\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/105198-roverdude/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@RoverDude\u003C/a\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002275006\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@NathanKell\u003C/a\u003E Nice work on the native telecommunications system. Looking forward to trying this. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E I like how one of the control points can be a nearby craft with a pilot aboard instead of requiring a connection all the way back to Kerbin. Makes for some interesting scenarios that way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m also curious to know if Squad has any plans for Bigelow-type expandable modules that block attempts to put kerbals in them in the editor, but count towards contracts once fully expanded. Some of the stuff I\u0027ve had to do is pretty kludgy, and it would be nice to have a standard means to have parts with variable crew capacity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"metl","CreatedById":82406,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:26:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSuper stoked for the changes. The ladder slide bug fix is about time! As far as the vessels shifting places during warp, I thought that was just me so super excited to see that fixed! And the stock comms system sounds freaking fantastic! Awesome work Squad!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:32:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729769\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472158565\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155578\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Andem\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n32 minutes ago, Andem said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, how similar will it be to AntennaRange v.s. RemoteTech2?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s basically AntennaRange with occlusion (line of sight) and partial control loss.\u00A0 It\u0027s nothing like RT.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vallius","CreatedById":100188,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:33:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny plans to empower the scientists and particularly engineers now that pilots are so essential?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:34:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeeing people complain about it now being difficult to control a probe not connected to a control point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that was the idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jarin","CreatedById":71395,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:35:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729816\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472160760\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s basically AntennaRange with occlusion (line of sight) and partial control loss.\u00A0 It\u0027s nothing like RT.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do like how KSP is getting \u0022lite\u0022 versions of features that had previously been mod-only (ISRU, Comms). \u00A0Here\u0027s hoping for a simple life support implementation somewhere down the line.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:36:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729820\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472160905\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002271395\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jarin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Jarin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s hoping for a simple life support implementation somewhere down the line.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hope not.\u00A0 Life support and KSP do not fit together, it adds tedium and no gameplay.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lloigor","CreatedById":164206,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:45:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729561\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472150605\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266485\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SQUAD\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, SQUAD said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n[...] and fixing some issues with the buildings at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E and KSC2 turning different colors.\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSC2? Can someone explain this please?\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:48:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729832\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472161522\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022164206\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lloigor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Lloigor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSC2? Can someone explain this please?\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a seeeecret!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe old \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E from early versions of the game can be found on Kerbin.\u00A0 No, it\u0027s not the island runway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-25T21:49:14Z\u0022 title=\u002208/25/2016 09:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Alshain\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbuvim","CreatedById":160177,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:48:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729832\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472161522\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022164206\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lloigor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Lloigor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSC2? Can someone explain this please?\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u00A0is a broken \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E on isle near, I think so.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-25T21:52:07Z\u0022 title=\u002208/25/2016 09:52  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Kerbuvim\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbuvim","CreatedById":160177,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:01:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729823\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472160980\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hope not.\u00A0 Life support and KSP do not fit together, it adds tedium and no gameplay.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLifesupport means more realism and makes the long flights\u00A0is much more challenging.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-25T22:02:22Z\u0022 title=\u002208/25/2016 10:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Kerbuvim\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FullMetalMachinist","CreatedById":156531,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:02:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729796\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472160150\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158329\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022OrbitalBuzzsaw\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n38 minutes ago, OrbitalBuzzsaw said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith you on that one! Although personally I think that we shouldn\u0027t have this whole stock RemoteTech thing at all, it\u0027s a bad precedent.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy a bad precedent? If you don\u0027t want it, just turn it off. It\u0027s been said several times that it will be controllable via difficulty settings.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI for one am very much looking forward to it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:07:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472162491\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160177\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbuvim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Kerbuvim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLifesupport means more realism and makes the long flights\u00A0is much more challenging.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI disagree on both counts.\u00A0 But this thread isn\u0027t about life support.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbuvim","CreatedById":160177,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:12:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472162863\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI disagree on both counts.\u00A0 But this thread isn\u0027t about life support.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis tread\u00A0about the further development of the game, including.\u00A0The absence of the concept of \u0022life-support\u0022 is almost tantamount to an endless fuel,\u00A0also makes the game too easy. Besides, life support can be made optional.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Skalou","CreatedById":133496,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:14:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729561\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472150605\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266485\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SQUAD\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, SQUAD said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n[...]partial control, which can happen when a probe or crewed pod without a pilot has no connectivity to a control point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbes will be limited to no throttle or full throttle,[...]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0022t care, i will drive the power by tweaking the thrust limiter slider in the right click menu, AHAHA! you did\u0027nt thought about it right? right? Uuh now you know... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:0.0:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_shocked.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:0.0:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd just got an other (dumb?) idea about it, what do you think guys about hidind the navball when under partial control, both in flight and map view? so come back to a real aproxiamate manoeuver, forcing you to take more care about the environment to orientate the craft, estimate the speed,... and still better than no control at all. because for now the malus shouldn\u0027t change anything a lot for me, even if i can\u0027t wait to try it as! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HoloYolo","CreatedById":138353,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:15:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729864\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472163173\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160177\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbuvim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Kerbuvim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis tread\u00A0about the further development of the game, including.\u00A0The absence of the concept of \u0022life-support\u0022 is almost tantamount to an endless fuel,\u00A0also makes the game too easy. Besides, life support can be made optional.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLife support should stay a mod. This game isn\u0027t meant to be 100% realistic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Redneck","CreatedById":2030,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:15:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729578\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472151159\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002271395\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jarin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Jarin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny word on PorkJet\u0027s work with the rocket-part models?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes I would like to know also. Ive asked this question in 4 different devnotes this being the 5th. Squad will not answer this question. Why?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T22:20:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729869\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472163344\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222030\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Redneck\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Redneck said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes I would like to know also. Ive asked this question in 4 different devnotes this being the 5th. Squad will not answer this question. Why?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey aren\u0027t answering the question because it\u0027s not coming in the next version.\u00A0 If it were, we would have heard before QA started.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}